2) proof of payment for the studies or a document confirming that the Foreigner studies free of charge;
3) current confirmation of the health insurance in the meaning of the Act of August 27, 2004 on benefits of health care financed from public funds or a valid confirmation that the treatment costs have been covered by the insurer along with a payment proof;
4) valid documents confirming that a Foreigner has enough financial means to pay for the maintenance costs, living costs and costs of return travel to their country of origin or residence or any costs of transit to a third country, such as a traveler's check; a certificate of the limit on the credit card issued by the bank that issued the credit card; certificate of holding by the foreigner or a person who sustains the Foreigner, cash means in a bank or a cooperative credit union with its office in the Republic of Poland or any other EU Member State, Member State of the European Free Trade Association (EFTA) - a party to the Agreement on the European Economic Zone or Swiss Confederation; a document confirming award of a national or international grant; a certificate of being hired and a certificate of salary earned by a foreigner or a person who sustains the Foreigner. The documents must be issued not later than a month before submitting a request for temporary stay permit but upon issuing a certificate of no amounts due to the University.
